<plot>A documentary about spivs in Britain in the aftermath of the Second World War, and the British attitudes towards them during these post-war years of severity. Some people saw these dealers as resourceful entrepreneurs; others believed them to be ruthless criminals. Includes a look at the portrayal of spivs in British culture, such as Pte. Joe Walker in _"Dad's Army" (1968)_ (qv).</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?510772</url></doc>
